**Attack Scenario**:
```javascript
// Attacker sends
POST /api/configure
{
  "config": {
    "__proto__": { "isAdmin": true },
    "debugMode": true
  }
}

// Results in:
Object.prototype.isAdmin = true  // ALL objects now have isAdmin=true
```

**Recommended Fix**:
```typescript
function safeAssign(target: any, source: any): void {
  if (!source || typeof source !== 'object') return;

  for (const key of Object.keys(source)) {
    if (key === '__proto__' || key === 'constructor' || key === 'prototype') {
      continue;  // Skip dangerous keys
    }
    target[key] = source[key];
  }
}

// Or use:
const config = Object.create(null);  // No prototype
Object.assign(config, incomingConfig);
```

